uiEntry.tooltip: Crane's Wing||Balanced army defence formation. Right-click for more information.

uiEntry.tooltip: Flying Geese||Cavalry heavy defence formation. Right-click for more information.

uiEntry.title: Reclining Dragon
uiEntry.tooltip: Reclining Dragon||Melee infantry heavy attack formation. Right-click for more information.

uiEntry.title: War of the Tiger
uiEntry.tooltip: War of the Tiger||Melee infantry heavy defence formation. Right-click for more information.

uiEntry.title: Bark of the Pine Tree
uiEntry.tooltip: Bark of the Pine Tree||Cavalry heavy attack formation. Right-click for more information.

uiEntry.title: Cloud Dragon
uiEntry.tooltip: Cloud Dragon||Missile heavy attack formation. Right-click for more information.

uiEntry.title: Flying Bird
uiEntry.tooltip: Flying Bird||Missile heavy defence formation. Right-click for more information.

uiEntry.title: Double Line Standard
uiEntry.tooltip: Double Line Standard||This is a balanced army formation, placing line infantry in the centre of the line and artillery in support. Light infantry and cavalry are placed on the flanks. A second line of infantry in the centre helps provide depth and the general is behind this line.

uiEntry.title: Grand Battery
uiEntry.tooltip: Grand Battery||This is a defensive artillery-heavy formation which places all artillery at the front in the centre. Light infantry are placed on the flanks of the artillery, and a line of infantry behind the artillery and light infantry. Cavalry are placed behind both lines on the flanks and the general is behind both lines in the centre.

uiEntry.title: Cavalry Heavy Right
uiEntry.tooltip: Cavalry Heavy Right||This is a cavalry-heavy formation designed to overload one side of the enemies formation. The centre is line infantry with artillery on the flanks as support. The cavalry is then placed on the extreme right flank and light infantry on the extreme left flank. The general brings up the rear of the army.

uiEntry.title: Cavalry Heavy Left
uiEntry.tooltip: Cavalry Heavy Left||This is a cavalry-heavy formation designed to overload one side of the enemies formation. The centre is line infantry with artillery on the flanks as support. The cavalry is then placed on the extreme left flank and light infantry on the extreme right flank. The general brings up the rear of the army.

uiEntry.title: Melee Frontline
uiEntry.tooltip: Melee Frontline||This is an infantry-heavy formation for use with lots of melee units. The melee units are placed in the front and are backed up by line infantry. Artillery are put on the flanks of the melee units and light infantry on the extreme flanks of the formation. Cavalry are placed behind the light infantry. The general is at the back of the formation in the centre.

uiEntry.title: Artillery Cross Fire
uiEntry.tooltip: Artillery Cross Fire||This is a formation for an artillery-heavy army. Line infantry are placed in the centre with light infantry on their flanks in support. Artillery is placed on the extreme flanks to provide a crossfire, and cavalry provide support to them. The general is at the back of the formation in the centre.

uiEntry.title: Line Astern
uiEntry.tooltip: Line Astern||The line astern formation arranges your grouped ships one behind the other. As the ships move past the enemy they will fire off a broadside one by one. This formation particularly suits ships with large numbers of guns on their broadsides.

uiEntry.title: Line Abreast
uiEntry.tooltip: Line Abreast||The line abreast formation arranges your grouped ships into a single line, abreast of each other - hence the name. It will still work with ships that fire broadsides, but you must manually move them into position to fire. Line abreast particularly suits ships with guns mounted in their noses, such as the Kotetsu.

uiEntry.title: button_repair
uiEntry.tooltip: Repair||Click this button to start ship repairs.||While repairs are being made, the ship will be unable to move or fire its guns.||As such, it is best to move it out of direct battle while repairs are being carried out.||Repairs will help the ship last longer in battle and any repairs carried out during battle will not cost anything.

uiEntry.title: pause
uiEntry.tooltip: Pause||Select this button to pause the game.||You can use the pause button to study the battle and plan your strategy.||While the game is paused you can still move the camera around and give orders.||Once the game is unpaused it the orders you have given will be carried out.

uiEntry.title: slow_mo
uiEntry.tooltip: Slow motion||Clicking this button will put the game into slow motion mode.||Slow motion mode gives you the chance to really revel in the glories of war!

uiEntry.title: play
uiEntry.tooltip: Play||This will unpause the game or return it to normal speed.

uiEntry.title: fwd
uiEntry.tooltip: Forward||Click this button to speed up the game by x2.||Click the play button to return to normal speed.||Speeding up the game is useful when you have made a move that allows you to sit and wait.||For example, chasing down fleeing enemies.||Use this button carefully - if you are in the middle of a complicated battle something might go wrong and speed by before you have a chance to correct it!

uiEntry.title: ffwd
uiEntry.tooltip: Fast Forward||Click this button to speed up the game by x4.||Click the play button to return to normal speed.||Speeding up the game is useful when you have made a move that allows you to sit and wait.||For example, chasing down fleeing enemies.||Use this button carefully - if you are in the middle of a complicated battle something might go wrong and speed by before you have a chance to correct it!

uiEntry.title: activate_ping
uiEntry.tooltip: Activate ping||Ping is used to give instructions to your allies. This button will display the different ping modes.

uiEntry.title: standard_ping
uiEntry.tooltip: Standard ping||Right-click to place ping on the battlefield.||This mode is used to draw your allies' attention to a specific area on the battlefield.

uiEntry.title: move_ping
uiEntry.tooltip: Move ping||Right-click to place ping on the battlefield.||This mode is used to instruct your allies to move to a specific area on the battlefield.

uiEntry.title: attack_ping
uiEntry.tooltip: Attack ping||Right-click to place ping on the battlefield.||This mode is used to instruct your allies to attack at a specific area on the battlefield.

uiEntry.title: defend_ping
uiEntry.tooltip: Defend ping||Right-click to place ping on the battlefield.||This mode is used to instruct your allies to defend a specific area on the battlefield.
